advanced technology class of targets, enabling mid-term employment of directed energy weapons. Specific activities within
this FY include delivering an updated tool for performing probabilistic/deterministic laser risk assessment of airborne laser
target designators, and completing general software tool updates to the Military Advanced Technology Integrated Laser Hazard
Assessment (MATILDA) model based on user community feedback to support the F-35 Joint Program Office and an United
Kingdom Project Agreement.
